cs.IR, cs.DL, cs.CR, cs.DB, cs.CL 

This paper is likely to belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category as it deals with the cached contents of search engines and their indexing strategies. It could also belong to the Digital Libraries (cs.DL) sub-category as it discusses building reliable preservation services from search engine caches. Additionally, it could be classified under the sub-categories of Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) and Databases (cs.DB) as it deals with the overlap of various caches and holdings of the Internet Archive. Finally, it could also be classified under the sub-category of Computation and Language (cs.CL) as it examines the MIME type of cached resources.
